description: Core stack, layout, and guardrails for meavo-navigation (@meavo/navigation)
alwaysApply: true
---

Environment: Shared npm package `@meavo/navigation` — the Meavo top nav + tool switcher consumed by every Meavo app. This is a **library**, not a Next.js app; nothing here runs standalone.

## Stack

- TypeScript strict, React 19; Next.js and `@prisma/client` are peer dependencies only
- Tailwind class names compiled by the consumer app (brand palette + `slate` must be resolvable there)
- tsup build → ESM `dist/` with two entries: `.` (client, `"use client"` banner) and `./server`
- Published via git tags (`#vX.Y.Z`) and GitHub Packages; `prepare` builds on git installs

## Do NOT

- Add runtime `dependencies` — react, next, `@prisma/client` stay peer deps / tsup externals
- Import `@prisma/client` or `@meavo/db` directly — use the structural `NavigationPrisma` type
- Put server-only code anywhere reachable from `src/index.ts` (client entry is one `"use client"` bundle)
- Show tools a non-admin user lacks `ToolCardAccess` for in `getAccessibleTools`
- Use `linkedAppKey` for access decisions — only for resolving the "current" tool
- Add a Meavo app key in one place only — update `MeavoAppKey`, `isMeavoAppKey`, `APP_FALLBACK_LABELS`, `MEAVO_APP_HOSTS` together
- Edit `dist/` by hand; change public exports without updating `package.json` `exports` + `tsup.config.ts`

## Code layout

| Area | Path |
|------|------|
| Client components (nav bar, switcher, avatar) | `src/client/` |
| Server helpers (tool access, current tool) | `src/server/` |
| Shared types | `src/types.ts` |
| App key registry (labels, hosts) | `src/constants.ts` |
| Gateway URL helpers | `src/gateway-url.ts` |
| Entry points | `src/index.ts` (client), `src/server.ts` (server) |
| Build config | `tsup.config.ts` |

## Data flow

```
Consumer app (server):
  getAccessibleTools(prisma, { userId, isAdmin, gatewayUrl })
    → ToolCard rows filtered by ToolCardAccess (admins see all active)
    → [gateway entry, ...tools]
  resolveCurrentToolId(options, MEAVO_APP_KEY) → currentId
Consumer app (layout):
  <MeavoNavBar links logoHref toolSwitcher userName signOutAction />
Browser:
  ToolSwitcher click → navigateToTool(url)
    → *.meavo.app host: same tab | anything else: new tab (noopener)
```

Every public-API change must be released: bump `package.json` version → tag `vX.Y.Z` → push tags → bump git ref in consumer repos.

